    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-18T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-18T14:00:00-05:00" n="85"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d85">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–1851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the United States Delegation to the
                        General Assembly</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-18T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 18, 1951—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 724. Subj: <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                        >SC</gloss> elections. Gross just raised with Gundersen (Norway) problem of
                    breaking deadlock on <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> voting so Council cld
                    function as of Jan 1. Gundersen’s reply indicated he does not have authority to
                    switch to Greece if deadlock continues. He also said they wld have to take
                    Denmark with them on any switch, indicating Denmark likewise does not have such
                    authority. Gundersen said he appreciated force of this new argument and wld
                    communicate it urgently to his capital. He said if deadlock does continue he
                    will <pb facs="0153" n="131" xml:id="pg_131"/> request authority to switch but
                    indicated difficulty of problem for them. Suggest <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> take up matter urgently with <gloss target="#t_Amb1"
                        >Amb</gloss>s and capitals.</p>
                <p>Sent <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 724, rptd info Oslo 50, Copenhagen
                    37.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
